<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-21T16:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-21T16:30:00-05:00" n="771" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d771">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3131/128: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Nicholson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-21T17:00:00-04:30">October 21, 1937—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>101. Department’s telegram No. 58, October 20, 6 p.m. Simultaneous
                            announcement that negotiations are contemplated will be issued by the
                            Venezuelan Government for publication Tuesday morning October 26.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Nicholson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>